&gt; Ole,
&gt; 
&gt;  
&gt; 
&gt; I am not sure if you can do that in Maven.  But I
&gt; think it might be
&gt; worth thinking about passing in the base folder to
&gt; your class under test
&gt; (Dependency Injection Pattern) rather than having
&gt; the class computing
&gt; it.  In situations like that I sometime use in my
&gt; class under test a
&gt; setter method for a base folder that I only use in a
&gt; test environment.
&gt; The class under test checks if the folder is already
&gt; set, if not, it
&gt; does the standard behavior in computing the current
&gt; folder, etc. You
&gt; could have a check for null and since the setter
&gt; method is not used in
&gt; production, the variable would be null in
&gt; production.
